# Commit messages

When creating git commits in this project:

- Use a **subject line only** (no body unless the user asks for one)
- Write in **imperative mood** ("Add", "Fix", "Remove", "Update")
- **Do not** use Conventional Commits prefixes (`feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor(theme):`, etc.)
- Keep subjects concise and specific to the change
- Split work into small, logical commits when appropriate

## Good

- Add useTheme hook
- Apply theme via inline script in root layout
- Remove ThemeProvider from page tests

## Bad

- feat(theme): add useTheme hook
- Added useTheme hook
- fix: theme flash on load
